==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Antimonious
<hw>An`ti*mo"ni*ous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or derived from, antimony; --
said of those compounds of antimony in which this element has an
equivalence next lower than the highest; <as>as, <ex>antimonious</ex>
acid</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antimonite</ent>⟦br⟧
